The InterContinental Hotel Nairobi held an activity on Saturday at the SOS Children&rsquo;s Village in Buruburu, Nairobi.The event was in an effort to spread New Year's festive joy to the children by presenting them with gifts.The gifts were bought by the hotel&rsquo;s guests and staff according to the children&rsquo;s wishes received by the hotel during festivities. Each child had previously submitted a gift request that did not exceed Sh2,500.Present were InterCon&rsquo;s resident manager Oliver Geyer and SOS Children&rsquo;s Village deputy national director and head of programmes Joseph Kajwang.The SOS Children&rsquo;s Village in Buruburu provides a residence to 267 children.